    <item>
      <title>Hmm... shields... bash hate... I wonder...</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=18976#M18976</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;Taken from TenFon's exhaustive parses on &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=paladinbalance&amp;message.id=18854"&gt;http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=paladinbalance&amp;amp;message.id=18854&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Hate by Bash is same as left hand weapon. For bash, Damage is same as Shield AC, but 22 is max of Bash Damage. Bash dose not have Damage Bonus, so Bash makes max 22 Hate with 22 or higher AC Shield. Low AC shiled makes lower Hate Bash. 2 Hand Bash (Knight AA Skill Bash without shield) makes 6 Hate. Furious Bash focus increse Bash Hate, but the value is random as same as Heal / DD focus. Shield with Furious Bash III makes average 25.5 Hate.&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Notice the part about 22 being the max, regardless of the shield AC value? Scaling, and then capped at a value so low that it hasn't be higher end for years? That sounded too simlar to the problems with taunt to be coincidence to me, so I started looking at bash hate without a cap, and several things suddenly made sense.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Furious Bash...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Vanilla 25ac shield from original EQ, with 25ac&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;22 hate (capped) = 22 hate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Highest end FB shield from today's EQ with 110ac and FB7&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;22 hate (capped) x 1.7 (FB7) = 37 hate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So, we've gone from:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;22 hate per bash cycle to compensate for the offhand agro generated by a SSotY or PGT, to&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;37 hate per bash cycle to compensate for the offhand agro generated by a Swiftcleave or Dual auged Epic2.0&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The bash difference being so negligable compared to the vast offhand differences, that you wonder why on earth the bothered with the line. But remove the cap:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Vanilla 25ac shield from original EQ, with 25ac&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;25 hate (capped) = 22 hate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Highest end FB shield from today's EQ with 110ac and FB7&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;110 hate (capped) x 1.7 (FB7) = 187 hate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now you've got a much more viable comparision between the offhand agro generation increases since pre-Kunark times, and the FB line actually enough of a provides a benefit to make it worthwhile to look for shields with it on.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Then I looked at the shield block AAs warriors got, which always confused me as a shield is very situational and hit with the double whammy of huge loss in dps coupled with huge loss in agro. This didn't really tally with the other two tank classes who suffered a much lower dps reduction, and very little agro reduction. Remove the cap on bash hate and suddenly the agro reduction is reduced greatly. We still suffer the major dps reduction but some of our offhand melee and proc agro is compensated. This would make shields a much more viable alternative, although since it would benefit knights to the same degree you'd have to establish whether 'agro with shield' between the two classes would remain balanced. Knights have already been agro balanced assuming they're using a shield while tanking, whereas warriors are assumed to be DWing where agro is a concern, so bash hate seems largely ignored.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Removing this cap has the potential to open up shield use to the warrior class as a viable alternative to DWing, and without the need for any sort of complex 'shieldmate' itemisation. Obviously balance would be needed to check the extra agro makes enough of a difference, whilst at the same time remaining a compromise, as well as agro balance versus knights since they're assumed to use shields whever they're tanking already. The existance of this cap however does seem to explain a lot of the inconsistancies I feel exist with FB and to a lesser extent, shield block&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So my question to the devs is this: Does the cap on bash hate (as parsed by TenFold) exist, and was it overlooked when creating Furious Bash, the subsequent extensions to the line, and shield block AAs for warriors?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
