      <description>Removing any caps on bash hate generation wouldn't make shields equivalent to dual wielding for aggro generation (hence there'd be little motivation for bandoliering out every 6 seconds for a bash), but certainly would give people a reason to hit the bash hotkey, and may make shield use a bit more practical.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It may also be reasonable to consider increasing the damage cap on bash, not just hate... it was revamped a very long time ago now to its current limit (scales with shield ac to I think 15 ac, and is capped past that), making shields essentially a 15/60 weapon, unhastable, with no double attack, which is of course a rediculously small amount of damage output in today's EQ.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
